  "rationale": "<p>Choice B is correct. A linear function has a constant rate of change, and any two rows of the table shown can be used to calculate this rate. From the first row to the second, the value of <span class=\"italic\">x</span> is increased by 2 and the value of <span class=\"math-container\"><img align=\"middle\" role=\"math\" class=\"math-img\" src=\"data:image/png;base64,\" alt=\"f of x\"></span> is increased by <span class=\"math-container\"><img align=\"middle\" role=\"math\" class=\"math-img\" src=\"data:image/png;base64,\" alt=\"6 equals, 4 minus negative 2\"></span>. So the values of <span class=\"math-container\"><img align=\"middle\" role=\"math\" class=\"math-img\" src=\"data:image/png;base64,\" alt=\"f of x\"></span> increase by 3 for every increase by 1 in the value of <span class=\"italic\">x</span>. Since <span class=\"math-container\"><img align=\"middle\" role=\"math\" class=\"math-img\" src=\"data:image/png;base64,\" alt=\"f of 2, equals 4\"></span>, it follows that <span class=\"math-container\"><img align=\"middle\" role=\"math\" class=\"math-img\" src=\"data:image/png;base64,\" alt=\"f of, open parenthesis, 2 plus 1, close parenthesis, equals, 4 plus 3, which equals 7\"></span>. Therefore, <span class=\"math-container\"><img align=\"middle\" role=\"math\" class=\"math-img\" src=\"data:image/png;base64,\" alt=\"f of 3, equals 7\"></span>.<p>Choice A is incorrect. This is the third <span class=\"italic\">x</span>-value in the table, not <span class=\"math-container\"><img align=\"middle\" role=\"math\" class=\"math-img\" src=\"data:image/png;base64,\" alt=\"f of 3\"></span>. Choices C and D are incorrect and may result from errors when calculating the function&rsquo;s rate of change.</p></p>\n",
